<h1>Aaron Vegh</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://aaron.vegh.ca/now/">aaron.vegh.ca/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Whitby
Ont
Canada
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
I run my own contracting business (Innoveghtive Inc.). Technically I’m the CEO, but when I’m selling my services it’s under the title “iOS, Mac and Web Developer"
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I create new products, and help others do the same.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I love technology, and I love to write code. Solving problems, making things work. Making beautiful products that people want to use. 
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
You’re on your own. Only you can solve your own problems. Others can help but you can’t rely on them to have your best interests at heart.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
The Three-Body Problem by Cixin Liu: <a href="http://www.amazon.ca/The-Three-Body-Problem-Cixin-Liu/dp/0765377063">http://www.amazon.ca/The-Three-Body-Problem-Cixin-Liu/dp/0765377063</a>
</p>

